In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reports that he has issued an Executive Order to take additional steps regarding the national emergency declared in previous Executive Orders. The order authorizes the imposition of sanctions on foreign financial institutions that have conducted significant transactions for or on behalf of certain Russian military-industrial sectors. It also prohibits the importation and entry into the United States of certain products from the Russian Federation, including fish, seafood, diamonds, and other products mined, extracted, produced, or manufactured in Russia. The order grants the Secretary of Homeland Security the authority to prescribe rules and regulations to enforce these importation prohibitions. President Biden encloses a copy of the Executive Order with his report.